Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Thinly slice the @tomato{2}(thinly sliced).

Drain and thinly slice the @mozzarella{125%g}(thinly sliced). Halve the @baguette{2} lengthways. Butter the bread if you like with @?butter{to taste}.

Pop the baguettes —cut-side up—into the #oven{} to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: To avoid turning on your oven, you can warm the baguette in the toaster instead.

Spread the @green pesto{1%sachet} onto the cut side of the base of each baguette. Top with the @salad leaves{40%g} (as much or as little as you like).

Lay the tomato, then the mozzarella on top of the salad. Drizzle some @oil{to taste} and the @balsamic glaze{1%sachet} over the top.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Sandwich closed with the top half of the baguette.

To serve, slice each baguette in half widthways. Divide between plates. Serve any remaining salad on the side.